#%% md
# User Feedback Theme Mining

## 1. Project Overview
**Task:** Cluster app-store reviews into themes to identify praise, complaints, and feature requests.
**Stack:** `LangChain` + `ChatOllama` + `qwen3.5:9b`.
#%% md
## 2. Why This Matters
- Prioritize product improvements based on feedback volume
- Surface feature requests for the roadmap
- Automated analysis saves hours of manual review reading
#%% md
## 3. Setup
#%%
import os, json, re, warnings
os.environ["TOKENIZERS_PARALLELISM"] = "false"
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

from langchain_ollama import ChatOllama
from langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage, SystemMessage

LLM_MODEL = "qwen3.5:9b"
llm = ChatOllama(model=LLM_MODEL, temperature=0)

def clean(text):
    if "<think>" in text: text = text.split("</think>")[-1].strip()
    return text.strip()

def ask(system, user):
    return clean(llm.invoke([SystemMessage(content=system), HumanMessage(content=user)]).content)

print(f"LLM ready: {ask('Reply OK.', 'Test')[:20]}")
#%% md
## 4. App Store Reviews
#%%
REVIEWS = [
    {"text": "App crashes every time I upload a photo!", "rating": 1},
    {"text": "Love the new dark mode feature", "rating": 5},
    {"text": "Why can't I export my data? Basic functionality", "rating": 2},
    {"text": "Search function is broken, never finds anything", "rating": 1},
    {"text": "Best productivity app, calendar sync is perfect", "rating": 5},
    {"text": "Battery drain is insane since last update", "rating": 2},
    {"text": "Please add widget support, would be 10/10", "rating": 4},
    {"text": "Dark mode great but notifications too loud", "rating": 3},
    {"text": "Keeps logging me out randomly every day", "rating": 1},
    {"text": "Onboarding tutorial was really helpful", "rating": 5},
    {"text": "Need offline mode badly, useless without internet", "rating": 2},
    {"text": "Smooth UI, fast loading, exactly what I needed", "rating": 5},
    {"text": "Photo upload fails on Android 14, please fix", "rating": 1},
    {"text": "Would love Slack integration for notifications", "rating": 4},
]
print(f"Reviews: {len(REVIEWS)}, Avg rating: {sum(r['rating'] for r in REVIEWS)/len(REVIEWS):.1f}")
